From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000004 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Boot Debug <noreply@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 30 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [DEBUG] cmdline: set udev.children_max=12 to match QLI1.8

QLI1.8 boots with udev.children_max=12 on the kernel cmdline, which lets
systemd-udevd run up to 12 worker processes in parallel (incl. in the
initramfs). The QLI2.0 cmdline does not set it, so udevd falls back to its
default worker cap. This patch appends udev.children_max=12 so the
initramfs "udevadm trigger + settle" stage can be compared against 1.8
under the same parallelism.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [boot-time experiment]
---
diff --git a/ci/performance.yml b/ci/performance.yml
index c3303684..00a54ad1 100644
--- a/ci/performance.yml
+++ b/ci/performance.yml
@@ -3,4 +3,4 @@ header:
 
 local_conf_header:
   cmdline-perf: |
-    KERNEL_CMDLINE_EXTRA:append = " quiet systemd.tty.term.console=linux"
+    KERNEL_CMDLINE_EXTRA:append = " quiet systemd.tty.term.console=linux udev.children_max=12"
